Key Match Events: Nathan Lukes drove in the winning run with a double in the eighth inning.
Davis Schneider hit a two-run home run in the fifth inning.
Lars Nootbaar homered for the Cardinals in the seventh inning.
Blue Jays second baseman Leo Jiménez made a diving stop and started an inning-ending double play in the sixth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Blue Jays manager John Schneider commented on the team's focus and effort in sweeping the series.
Cardinals manager Oliver Marmol reflected on the team's offensive struggles.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Toronto Blue Jays' Chris Bassitt was given the Roberto Clemente Award before the game.
